「...Well, that should do it.」

I've just finished patching up a number of holes that I hadn't discovered until the rain yesterday brought them to light.

There might still be plenty more holes that I still haven't found yet, as well as all sorts of other problems, but this should do for now.

No matter how much time I spend fixing, there's always a new problem to be solved.

In the end, I decided to fix the problems as they appear.

Now, I can finally relax a bit, and go back to deciphering the old books abandoned in this cabin.

After that, I can go find some fruits, or something else suitable, to sell in the village. Astoundingly, I've managed to work out a tidy living out here.

...Still, right now, my livelihood depends on the weather.

Furthermore, I'm living on my own, in the middle of nowhere, with absolutely no savings, a rather concerning situation...

I have some wood left over. I could use it for my future repairs, or as firewood, but where to keep it until I need it...

「...I know.」

