First, I carefully taught them the right way to use the carving tools to avoid hurting themselves. Then, I gave each of them a small knife to chip away at the wood.

It took some time to get going, but eventually, I managed to teach them the basics...

After a while, they all got quite into it, and quieted down, concentrating on the work. This is much easier, compared to how they're usually tagging along behind me.

...This is nice.

Next time that they're bothering me, I'll just distract them by getting them to carve again.

Hinata and Ibara are both making flowers, and Tsukiyo is making a bug.

When I asked Konomi what he's making, he just laughed and said "it's a secret"...

「Alright, done.」

I mutter to myself, my handmade flower hair piece finished.

「...」

Normally, they'd all be crowding around me, going "You're done? Let me see, let me see", but right now they're all working so hard they haven't even noticed.

...I actually feel a little lonely that they're ignoring me, but I know that's just being selfish.

Well then, let's go see how they're doing.

